    "The networks are trained using three losses: the autoencoder reconstruction loss L A, the linear dynamics loss L R, and the future state prediction loss L F.L A = 1 2(n + 1) n+1 i=1 ||x(t i) -d N N (e N N (x(t i); θ e); θ d)|| 2 2 (21) L R = 1 2n n i=1 ||e N N (x(t i+1); θ e) -Ae N N (x(t i); θ e)|| 2 2 (22)L F = 1 2n n i=1 ||x(t i+1) -d N N ( Ae N N (x(t i); θ e); θ d)|| 2 2 (23)C = κ A L A + κ R L R + κ F L F (24)The cost function C is composed of a weighted sum of the loss terms L A, L R, L F and weighting terms κ A, κ R, κ F. Furthermore, [216] allows A to vary depending on the state.",
    "This is achieved by predicting the eigenvalues of A with an auxiliary network and constructing the matrix from these.",
    "Active learning and transfer learningFinally, an important machine learning technique independent of the NN architecture and applicable to both spacetime and time-stepping approaches is active learning [218].Instead of precomputing a labeled data set, data is only provided when the prediction quality of the NN is insufficient.",
